[The species _Cowpox virus_ is a member of the genus _Orthopoxvirus_
of the sub-family _Chordopoxvirinae_ of the family _Poxviridae_. The
species name cowpox virus is a misnomer since it is not naturally
present in bovines but occurs predominantly in rodents. Cowpox virus
in fact has a broad host range and has been isolated from felines,
dogs, elephants and humans as well as bovines. Genome sequence
analysis has suggested that cowpox virus is closest to a hypothetical
ancestral poxvirus from which other orthopoxviruses have evolved. The
preceding report makes the interesting observation that the
appearance of cowpox virus in human hosts may increase with overall
resistance to orthopoxvirus infection as a consequence of the
cessation of smallpox (vaccinia) vaccination. - Mod.CP]
